    longDescription:
      "Production RL pricing models face two distinct failure modes: cap-boundary trapping, where the model gets frozen at a constraint boundary and loses the ability to respond when the optimum shifts; and overshooting, where simultaneous reactions from multiple teams compound before the combined effect can be observed. A third concern is headroom — if the RL crowds out available treatment range by pushing to caps across the board, human-designed pricing campaigns have no room to operate. Two complementary slowdown mechanisms were built: a cap-based mechanism combining threshold reduction and minimum step size (selected via cost simulation), and a multiplicative three-factor environment-change detection function monitoring profit margin, breakeven investment, and price competitiveness per region.",
