    longDescription:
      "The pricing system's fixed winsorization threshold clipped bookings uniformly across all destination markets, but a booking that's an outlier in a smaller market may be ordinary in a high-volume one — systematically blunting signal from smaller markets while under-clipping larger ones. An additional constraint was computational: the pricing dataset is large and multiple optimization processes run concurrently, so any replacement had to remain lightweight enough for production scale. The project replaced the fixed threshold with a two-parameter linear formula — threshold as a function of revenue per booking — fitted to equalize remaining signal percentage across destinations. The redesign narrowed the spread of remaining signal from ~17 to ~8 percentage points without degrading signal detection quality.",
